column61: Large group, spread out. Feeding/diving birds associated. "Y" for calf originally--ABD
Birds associated.
Lg. whl spotted by oceanographers near port stern as array being pulled in. Two staff saw small falcated dorsal on large whale: fin/sei?Lg balleen.
On station. Sono buoy heard sperm whale clicks.
Animals approached from stbd. Bow then from all directions.
Sm, low bushy blow. Fairly lg dorsal(2ft),med grey. Med body size. Possibly pseudorca?? Never had good look.
Lots of breaching, socializing in mixed group with Lo's. Came to ship and bowriding.
Lots of breaching, socializing in mixed group with Lb's. Came to ship and bowriding.
Came to ship as we pulled array.
Swimming around ship at station. Stayed for almost 10 min. Very close to same area as sgt. # 15 1.5 hours earlier.
deploying array. OFF EFFORT NOT UP TO SPEED
Mixed group: Dd/Dc. Observed 4 Dc.
Chin slapping.
Breaching near Dd/Dc sighting #20. Juvenile/sub-adult.
At station. Animals chasing fish around ship. Scales observed off bow.
Dd/Dc sighting #20 still around ship. Animals have broken into many smaller groups.
Resting at surface, no forward movement.
May be same group as sighting #23.
One adult and one juvenile/sub-adult travelling together.
Dolphins observed at horizon. Ship stopped at station before full ID could be made.
Same group as 05:50 sighting, #29.
Container ship closing in.
Off effort due to ship heading back to station at an angle due to ourse change for cargo ship avoidance.
Observed while looking for unid lg whale on big eyes. Saw only once. Looked like Lo.
Back on effort as we are back on transect line.
Most likely minke.
Detected animals on sonobuoy at station. Off effort.
Animlas looked to be feeding. No interest in vessel.
Came to ship at station: 83.80
Observed off stern while deploying sono buoy.
